    <note>Ma(2) Yuanfang [1355] His grandson Sui's [3668] first and second wives were both daughters of Duan(1) Zhen [3928] (sororate). The father-in-law of Sui's son, Ma(2) Xiyue [3666], was Du(3) Chun [1724]. Sui's grandsons all had the same generational names as Ma(2) Chengjia [1338] and Chengding [1339]. Ma(2) Chengxiu [3664], the son-in-law of Chao(2) Duanyan's [14] lineage cousin, Chao(2) Duanli [3023], has the same generational name as his great great grandsons. The authorship of Sui's funerary inscription further supports this conclusion. Chao Buzhi, WJ, 66.11b; XCB, 44.14a, 71.4a, 73.22a, 85.10b, 92.5a-5b; SS, 301.3b-4a. CBD, 3, 1833-4.</note>
